From: Miroslav Zagorac <mzagorac@haproxy.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 21:18:21 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] [EXPORTERS] Add MaybeSpawnBackgroundThread() to OTLP gRPC
 exporters

The gRPC channel stays in IDLE state until the first RPC is issued,
deferring DNS resolution, TCP handshake, TLS negotiation and HTTP/2
connection setup to the first export.

Added MaybeSpawnBackgroundThread() to OtlpGrpcClient which calls
channel->GetState(true) to transition the channel from IDLE to CONNECTING,
triggering gRPC's internal thread creation and connection setup.  Exposed
the method through all three OTLP gRPC exporter classes (traces, metrics,
logs) so callers can force an early connection immediately after
construction.
